        ") %>

          <h4>Searching</h4>
          <p>Searching is not case-sensitive.</p>
          <p>There are four record-level starting points for searches, along with tree searches, which operate a little differently.</p>
          <p/>The record-level search types are:
          <ul>
              <li/>Taxon Name
              <li/>Reference
              <li/>Author
              <li/>Instance
          </ul>
          </p>
          <p>Record-level searches can be simple or advanced.  A simple search is one in which you don't specify a field, so they look only at the default field.</p>
          <h5>Default fields for record-level searches</h5>
          <ul>
              <li/>Taxon Name: taxon full name
              <li/>Reference: citation
              <li/>Author: name or abbreviation (a match on either returns a result)
              <li/>Instance: taxon full name of the instance
          </ul>
